
1. Copy the files to your own directory.

2. Modify inet.h to reflect the host you are currently logged into.
   Also, modify the port numbers to be used to reduce the likelihood
   of conflicting with another server.

3. Compile the source code using the command: make

4. Start the directory server in one host in the foreground (./directoryServer2)

5. Start a chat server in another host in the foreground (make sure it has the same IP as directory server) (./chatServer2 <chat topic> <port>)

6. Start the client on another host in the foreground: ./chatClient2

7. Remember to kill the servers before logging off.
